OL,4,CLockdown weight gain averaging half a
OL,5,Cstone - survey
OL,6, More than 40% of adults in England have
OL,7, gained weight during the pandemic, a
OL,8, survey suggests, with the average gain
OL,9, being half a stone (just over 3kg).
OL,11,FPublic Health England (PHE), which
OL,12,Fsurveyed 5,000 people, says Covid
OL,13,Flockdowns and disrupted daily routines
OL,14,Fhave made it challenging for people to
OL,15,Feat healthy and keep fit.
OL,17,FSnacking and comfort eating were given
OL,18,Fas the main contributor by about half
OL,19,Fof those who said they were fatter.
OL,21,FPHE recommends a summer fitness drive.
